# Tracked copy of /etc/cron.d/ahg-facet-cache (source of truth). Heratio app cron.
# No AHG internal addresses/secrets present - tracked verbatim. Update after each edit.
# ============================================================================

# Heratio: hourly refresh of display_facet_cache for every DB that has the GLAM browse.
#
# Replaces the prior /usr/share/nginx/archive symfony cron (which only hit the
# `archive` DB and silently bypassed atom/dam/heratio). One outer flock so
# parallel runs can't pile up — that was the root cause of the 12-query, 25-hour
# stuck-query incident on 2026-04-28. max_execution_time=300000 (5 min) gives a
# server-side belt-and-braces if one DB's facet build hangs.
#
# Each DB is invoked sequentially. If one is slow, subsequent DBs that hour are
# delayed but the next hour's tick will skip (flock -n) until this run finishes,
# so backlog cannot recur.
#
# Absolute paths to php + artisan because /etc/cron.d/* commands run with
# cwd=/. The previous form (`php artisan ...`) silently failed every hour
# with "Could not open input file: artisan" - fixed 2026-05-06.
#
# Runs as www-data, NOT root. The artisan command lazy-creates Laravel cache
# shards under storage/framework/cache/data/<2c>/<2c>/ and root-owned shards
# break subsequent www-data writes (see docs/reference/github-pat-rotation.md
# pattern; concrete incident 2026-05-08 surfaced via /admin/errorLog as
# fopen(...c+) "No such file or directory" 500s on /api/ric/v1/* endpoints).
SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin
0 * * * * www-data flock -n /var/run/heratio-facet-cache.lock -c 'for d in archive atom dam heratio; do echo "[$(date -Iseconds)] facet-cache: $d"; DB_DATABASE=$d /usr/bin/php8.3 /usr/share/nginx/heratio/artisan ahg:refresh-facet-cache 2>&1 || echo "  failed $d"; done >> /var/log/facet-cache.log 2>&1'
